TextChange: If you have heard of a Fabrege egg, which is an egg that could buy you and sell you because it costs so much, what is it even?  A knick knack that collects dust.   It is really meaningless, but people will pay huge chunks of money for them.  I'd like to research why it costs so much to make them, and who really buys them, and why they buy them.  It seems like a status symbol only.   There is not a bar of gold inside, or money to pay your child's college tuition.  It is only beautiful on the outside with little substance on the inside. => T
